# Kit workflow

Read before non-trivial tasks when Agent Dev Kit is installed.

**User global rules** (`~/.cursor/rules/`) take precedence when stricter.

Before loading kit guidelines, read `~/.cursor/kit-user-rules.manifest.json` — see [kit-user-rules.mdc policy](../agent_dev_kit/docs/cursor-user-rules.md).

## Flow

0. Classify user message — [INTENT-ROUTING.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/INTENT-ROUTING.md) (text and `/feature` share the same pipeline; clarify if ambiguous).
1. Set **work_ref** / **spec_key** when a ticket exists — [TRACKER.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/TRACKER.md).
2. Follow [docs/guidelines/WORKFLOW.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/WORKFLOW.md).
3. **Spec first** — write `.ai/*-spec.md`, get human approval ([SPECS.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/SPECS.md)).
4. **Plan** — write `.ai/*-plan.md` with Detail: minimal | standard | detailed; wait for approval before production code.
5. **TDD** — implement per [TESTING.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/TESTING.md).
6. **Comprehension** — handoff + Q&A + human sign-off before verify ([COMPREHENSION.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/COMPREHENSION.md)).
7. **Verification** — separate agent session before commit ([VERIFICATION.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/VERIFICATION.md)).
8. **Review** — [REVIEW.md](../agent_dev_kit/docs/guidelines/REVIEW.md) before commit or PR.

